The paper deals with the problem of fingerprint presentation attack detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR). The use of 3D t-SNE visualization and clustering of material characteristics suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.MM) and data analysis (cs.LG). The proposal of an optimized Android app indicates a potential interest in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
